2. cs.AG (Algebraic Geometry): The paper talks about the closure of GL_{n^2}(C)-orbit of the determinant polynomial det_n with respect to linear substitution. This is a problem in algebraic geometry. 
3. cs.GR (Group Theory): The paper deals with the group GL_{n^2}(C) and its irreducible representations. This falls under the sub-category of Group Theory. 
4. cs.CO (Combinatorics): The paper talks about partitions and their properties. This is a combinatorial problem and hence falls under the sub-category of Combinatorics. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): This is the least likely sub-category as the paper does not deal with any algorithms or data structures.
